Peru:
Fujimori has for medical examinations once again to hospital
The former President Alberto Fujimori was on Tuesday in a public hospital in order to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72 - year-old Fujimori, 25 years in prison for violation of human rights during his reign (1990 - 2000), has several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, a member of Congress, and his personal doctor, told the television that Fujimori investigated in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas for three days, in order to determine the reason for his pain and muscle loss in the lower body.
Aguinaga commented that, in his opinion, Fujimori could be pardoned on humanitarian grounds, yet he does not want this, because he is innocent.
He was four times to cancer of the tongue, and he has lost 18 kilos weight. Other diseases, such as a severe erosive Gastritis, a Zyste in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and Durchblutungsprobleme in the legs, was one of the doctor.
Fujimori has since September 2007 in the penitentiary Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the Peruvian army death squad during his government, was convicted.
